I tried to add a Filter gadget from EACJ to Confluence (EAC), and got the following error:
{panel}
The selected filter filter-11350 has an error: Field 'fixVersion' does not exist..
{panel}

!http://img.skitch.com/20100225-kudb8cuat63m5uaxub33qfbicu.jpg!

Not sure if this is a config issue or a bug.

JIRA's XML importer should not exclude data if username doesn't exist in JIRA.

{code}
2010-04-06 17:18:15,618 http-8080-Processor25 INFO admin 61824x156x1 17ijxn http://localhost:8080/secure/admin/XmlRestore.jspa [jira.upgrade.tasks.UpgradeTask_Build319] Could not find author 'dyu' for filter with id '10373'
{code}

For example, what if a customer sets up a new instance for testing, and hasn't fully yet configured Crowd with all the users referenced in the JIRA XML backup.  She then restores this backup and finds that none of the favourites have been imported.

This results in users losing all their default dashboards if customer upgrades from a version < 3.13 to a version >= 3.13.

